<p>
	John and Dave are back at it, this time with not only answers to your questions, but a quick primer on iOS 7 for those of you that have updated or are just about to do so. Topics this week include managing your sharing settings so you know what data others can see, shutting down a pesky computer, trusting your iTunes purchase history, and answering a few questions about restoring from backups (always an important topic!). Download and enjoy!</p>
<p>
	<strong>Sponsor</strong>: <a href="http://filetransporterstore.com" data-wpel-link="external" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Transporter</a> is an off-cloud social storage drive for sharing, accessing and backing up your files in real time. Works with Mac, iPad, iPhone, or Windows. Use coupon code &#39;MGG&#39; for 10% off!</p>
